Australia beat New Zealand 26-24 in
Hong Kong today in the final game of the four-match Bledisloe
Cup competition.  The last time the Australians beat the All Blacks was in
July 2008.  The Wallabies, second in the International Rugby Boardâ€™s
ranking behind the All Blacks, ended a 15-match winning streak
by the New Zealanders. The match, the third time the teams have
met at a neutral venue, is the last clash of the year between
the trans-Tasman neighbors before end-of-year tours to Europe.  To contact the reporter on this story:
